We will cover prosodic/phonological features, then morphology and morphophonology in the major word classes, then look at syntactic structures, and finally use this knowledge to analyze spoken and written Pite Saami texts. Some basic language skills and insights into language community contexts will also be covered.Objectives/eesmärkid:  This course provides a synchronic overview of grammatical structures in Pite Saami (phonology, morphology and syntax)Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students will acquire knowledge of the language's structure and the context it is spoken in and be able to analyze Pite Saami texts, and use this knowledge to better understand, compare and contrast other Saamic and Uralic grammatical structures.
